'''张尔昌'''（'''{{lang|en|Gladstone Charles Fletcher Porteous}}'''，{{bd|1874年||1944年|11月}}），是一位澳洲籍[[新教|新教]]传教士，於1904年被[[中國內地會|中國內地會]]派往中国云南传教。他是一位專業《[[聖經|聖經]]》譯者，設計了[[彝语北部方言|彝语北部方言]]的拼音字母，並將《[[新約聖經|新約聖經]]》譯成數個中國方言版本。<ref>''Annual Report of the American Bible Society'' (American Bible Society, 1949) p. 133 "Gladstone Porteous – Mr. Porteous had completed the translation of the Nasu New Testament before Pearl Harbor and had it accepted by the China Bible House for publication. Only the first page of the manuscript was actually in the hands."</ref><ref>''The Tai Race, Elder Brother of the Chinese,'' ed. William Clifton Dodd, Isabella Ruth Eakin Dodd (1996) "A call was sent out by Mr. Gladstone Porteous, from Wutingchow, Yunnan. It was addressed to 'The Presbyterian Laos Mission, Bangkok, Siam,' and in due time it came to me."</ref><ref>''Among the Tribes in South-west China,''  Samuel R. Clarke (1984) p. 315 "Mr. Nicholls and Mr. and Mrs. Gladstone Porteous are kept very busy in the work. Difficulties many, and dangers not a few, beset the path. The Miao are low in the social scale. The landlords of their miserably barren farms are Chinese."</ref><ref>Marshall Broomhall ''The Jubilee Story of the China Inland Mission'' (China Inland Mission, 1915) p. 386 "In Yunnan Mr. Nicholls, who lost his wife in 1903, has had as colleagues Mr. and Mrs. Gladstone Porteous, Mr. G.E. Metcalf, and more recently Mr. and Mrs. Gowman."</ref><ref>[http://www.bdcconline.net/zh-hans/stories/by-person/g/gao-man.php 高漫 - 华人基督教史人物辞典] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bdcconline.net/zh-hans/stories/by-person/g/gao-man.php |date=20140116094912 }} 撒普山在云南府（今昆明市）以北，接近山区的一个村寨。1907年，郭秀峯教士（{{lang|en|Arthur G. Nicholls}}）和张尔昌教士夫妇（{{lang|en|Mr. & Mrs. Gladstone Porteous}}）在此地建立了</ref>

==早期生涯==
张尔昌原名'''格拉德斯通·查尔斯·弗莱彻·波蒂厄斯'''（{{lang|en|Gladstone Charles Fletcher Porteous}}），在[[澳洲|澳洲]][[维省|维省]]的卡根漢姆镇（{{lang|en|Carngham}}）的一个英国移民家庭出生。他的父亲约翰·邓普西-波蒂厄斯（{{lang|en|John Dempsey-Porteous}}）是携妻帶子从[[苏格兰|苏格兰]][[格拉斯哥|格拉斯哥]]迁来的。<ref>''China's Millions'' (China Inland Mission, Council for North America, 1906) "Nichols has had a new worker, Mr. Gladstone Porteous, from Australia, join him in the work at the south gate during the quarter. Mr. Porteous is now studying the language there, and giving such help as he can in the work."</ref>

==洒普山==
张尔昌青年时加入了英国[[内地会|内地会]]，並在位于[[墨尔本|墨尔本]]郊区[[里奇蒙_(维多利亚省)|里奇蒙]]的[[里霍博斯傳教士學院|里霍博斯傳教士學院]]（{{lang|en|Rehoboth Missionary College}}）接受培训。之後，张尔昌受内地会派遣，于1904年10月抵达[[廣州|廣州]]。於1906年，被內地會指派到[[雲南|雲南]][[武定县|武定县]][[洒普山|洒普山]]傳教，張爾昌於大約1915年抵達[[洒普山|洒普山]]。在此期間，張爾昌一邊學習中文，一邊憑藉著醫學知識和帶來的醫學儀器，爲當地苗人治病。<ref>Lachlan Strahan ''Australia's China: Changing Perceptions from the 1930s to the 1990s.'' p. 111.</ref>他的朋友們都稱张尔昌為「格拉迪」波蒂厄斯（{{lang|en|"Gladdie" Porteous}}）。<ref>Elinor Violet May Cook, ''Fijian Diary, 1904–1906: A Young Australian Woman's Account,'' 1996, p. 189 "Gladdie – Gladstone Porteous was an old friend of the Cook family who shared with them keen interest in missions. He himself served with the China lnland Mission."</ref>

==撒老坞==
1920年，張爾昌從洒普山輾轉到[[禄劝县|禄劝县]][[撒营盘镇|撒营盘镇]]的撒老坞村（又叫撒老乌或上罗婺），创办了[[彝族|纳苏颇]]（彝族的一支）教会'''撒老坞总堂'''（也叫撒老乌总堂）。在撒老坞期间，张尔昌学会一口流利的纳苏颇彝语。在苗人信徒[[李發獻|李發獻]]等人协助下，张尔昌利用[[柏格理苗文|柏格理苗文]]字母，創製了一套[[柏格理彝文|柏格理彝文]]（也叫黑彝文），並將《聖經·新約》全书翻譯成此种彝文，供纳苏颇彝族教会使用。而後他又翻譯了幾首[[讚美詩|讚美詩]]。<ref>Joakim Enwall ''A Myth become Reality: History and Development of the Miao written language''. Institute of Oriental Languages (Stockholm University, 1995) p. 241.</ref>

後來，张尔昌和米妮·波蒂厄斯（{{lang|en|Minnie Porteous}}）結婚，並育有三名子女：露絲·凱瑟琳（{{lang|en|Ruth Catherine}}）、克莉絲汀·奧利弗（{{lang|en|Christine Olive}}）和斯坦利·約翰（{{lang|en|Stanley John}}，二戰期間在澳大利亞皇家空軍時戰死）。<ref>张尔昌简介 云南苗族基督教网 2010年8月13日  张尔昌（Gladstone Porteous 1874–1944). 英籍澳大利亚人，基督教内地会传教士。1874年生于澳大利亚，1904年10月到中国传教，先在广州，1915年左右到 ... "</ref>

==死亡==
於1944年11月10日，70歲的張爾昌因[[斑疹傷寒|斑疹傷寒]]病發，死于撒老坞，葬于撒老坞总堂旁。當地教會成員為他豎立了一塊墓碑，而其中的成員事後描述製作墓碑時的情況：

{{Cquote|「我們的父親去世時，一塊大石板被人們切開，而人們則透過使用令人筋疲力盡，但成效令人驚訝的磨石方法來將大石板的表面拋光。然後，牧師在大石板上鑿上由三種語言組成的碑文—英文、[[彝族語言|彝文]]和中文，而石頭則被豎立在這些基督徒的墳墓上。"<ref>''A Tribute from a Friend'', quoted in biography of Gladstone Porteous by Ruth Porteous Bailey and Christine Porteous, in ''The Porteous Story'', 1975, Porteous Associates.</ref>}}

